abstract = {Background: Sepsis is an acute disease with high mortality and morbidity. Early and adequate drug therapy is critical when treating patients with sepsis. Individualized treatment of sepsis is crucial considering the different patient's phenotypes. Therefore, this paper aims to guide physicians to better individualize the treatment plan for their patients by developing a medical prediction model to predict the mortality rate of the patient and the recommended medication for the patient.Methods: The main methods used in this paper are Support Vector Machine, Decision Tree, Random Forest, Gradient Boosting, Logistic Regression, and Gaussian Naive Bayes, which are used to build a mortality prediction model using the indicators of ICU patients combined with the deaths of ICU patients, and to derive the effect of medications on the deaths of the patients.Results: The best predictive model for mortality was Extreme Gradient Boosting, with an accuracy of 0.802. Extreme Gradient Boosting also fitted the best drug prediction model with an accuracy of 0.867 in terms of heparin prediction.Conclusions: The paper concluded with machine learning methods to develop a prediction model for medication use in sepsis patients and showed 17 vital signs that affect mortality, including age, respiratory rate, etc. Also, Heparin, Acetaminophen, and Metoprolol Tartrate effectively treat sepsis patients. Norepinephrine, cefepime, and furosemide are related to high mortality because most uses are on severe patients. Hydromorphone is the drug that indeed increases mortality.},
